        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-07-12T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-07-12T18:00:00-05:00" n="267" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d267">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.20293/7–1248: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-07-12T19:00:00-04:00">July 12, 1948—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1018. Telegram Jul 6<note n="83" xml:id="d267fn83">Not found in Department
                        files.</note> ComNavPortFac Shanghai<note n="84" xml:id="d267fn84">Commander, Naval Port Facilities, Shanghai.</note> to ComNav-WesPae<note n="85" xml:id="d267fn85">Commander. U. S. Naval Forces in the Western
                        Pacific.</note> repeated CNO<note n="86" xml:id="d267fn86">Chief of Naval
                        Operations.</note> for info reports increasing number USSR citizens
                    proceeding Taiwan recent weeks including persons known have connection with
                    Soviet espionage agents. Telegram further states according Chinese intelligence
                    these persons ordered report <pb facs="0362" n="352" xml:id="pg_352"/> AAG
                    activities and while Chinese security organs endeavoring maintain close
                    surveillance not believed it will be sufficient.</p>
                <p>Emb requested discuss foregoing informally with FonOff and express Dept’s concern
                    this situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
